  "body": "Currently there seem to be an issue on some machine when opening encrypted database, the node crashes with:\r\n\r\n`unable to open database file`\r\n\r\nThis happens only with encrypted databases, so it's likely related to sqlcipher.\r\n\r\nThe machine I am running on is:\r\n\r\n`Linux 5.7.12-arch1-1 #1 SMP PREEMPT Fri, 31 Jul 2020 17:38:22 +0000 x86_64 GNU/Linux`\r\n\r\nNote that running the same code on the same machine using other platform works fine.\r\nTested with:\r\n- C generated bindings and a nodejs wrapper\r\n- Android emulator\r\n- Status-go code directly\r\n\r\nSo seems to be related to desktop.\r\n\r\nThe problem is present both on the released versions and running it locally from master.",
