    "body": "looking at systrace I found out the actual issues:\r\n`613918 openat(AT_FDCWD, \"/home/..../documents/programming/status/nim-status-client/data/app-307863656166663665363033376463343638353335643064316565346636326235313561363165616338616338623261346137636363333335656364393136623531.sql-journal\", O_RDWR|O_CREAT|O_CLOEXEC, 0644) = -1 ENAMETOOLONG (File name too long)`\r\n\r\nWhich is weird, as I can create files fine with larger filenames and interact with them from the command line. The partition is user-space encrypted so that might have an effect on it.\r\n\r\nRunning from `/tmp` gets me further, but still fails with `Login failed.Please re-enter your password and try again`\r\n",
